    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-16T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-16T08:00:00-05:00" n="886"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115(39)/311: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-16T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 16, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 16—8:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2647. Department’s 1609, December 15. London representative Lykes Brothers
                    advises that <hi rend="italic">Winston Salem</hi> was released under so-called
                    “Black Diamond” guarantee, namely that the company would return the cotton to
                    British port at their expense but not in the <hi rend="italic">Winston
                        Salem</hi>; in fact the cotton is now unloaded on the dock at Rotterdam and
                    it is planned to send the <hi rend="italic">Winston Salem</hi> direct to the
                    United States and to return the cotton to British port by coastal steamer. In
                    view of this, will not approach British authorities with regard to <hi
                        rend="italic">Winston Salem</hi> and will await further instructions. Is it
                    desired to make separate inquiry with regard to seizure of the cotton?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
